This paper is about improving the training and generalization of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on optimization methods, which is a subfield of machine learning that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The experiments in the paper involve image classification, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of blocks to improve the optimization method, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
